<p>I want to be able to set a min/max range and use it to check valid/invalid inputs while reading values from a file.</p>  <p>My min and max values in the first line are <em>1</em> and <em>10</em>, respectively. This is my text file to be tested (<em>num.txt</em>):</p>  <pre><code>1 10 2  4 5 </code></pre>  <p>In this program, I want to use <code>fscanf(stdin , ...)</code>:</p>  <pre><code>fscanf( stdin, "%d%c", &amp;num, &amp;c );     </code></pre>  <p>How can I read the first line and check it for the min and max values and then continue reading the following lines?</p>